{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<h2 id=\"css-modules-and-gatsby\"><a href=\"#css-modules-and-gatsby\" aria-label=\"css modules and gatsby permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>CSS modules and Gatsby</h2>\n<p>Gatsby works out of the box with CSS Modules. Here is an <a href=\"https://github.com/gatsbyjs/gatsby/tree/master/examples/using-css-modules\">example site that uses CSS modules</a>.</p>\n<h2 id=\"what-is-a-css-module\"><a href=\"#what-is-a-css-module\" aria-label=\"what is a css module permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>What is a CSS module?</h2>\n<p>Quoting from\n<a href=\"https://github.com/css-modules/css-modules\">the CSS Module homepage</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>A <strong>CSS Module</strong> is a CSS file in which all class names and animation names\nare scoped locally by default.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>CSS Modules are very popular as they let you write CSS like normal but with a lot\nmore safety. The tool automatically makes class and animation names unique so\nyou don’t have to worry about selector name collisions.</p>\n<h2 id=\"when-to-use-css-modules\"><a href=\"#when-to-use-css-modules\" aria-label=\"when to use css modules permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>When to use CSS modules</h2>\n<p>CSS Modules are highly recommended for those new to building with Gatsby (and\nReact in general).</p>\n<h2 id=\"how-to-build-a-page-using-css-modules\"><a href=\"#how-to-build-a-page-using-css-modules\" aria-label=\"how to build a page using css modules permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>How to build a page using CSS modules</h2>\n<p>Visit the <a href=\"https://www.gatsbyjs.org/tutorial/part-two/#css-modules\">CSS Modules section of the tutorial</a> to learn how to build a page using CSS modules.</p>","excerpt":"CSS modules and Gatsby Gatsby works out of the box with CSS Modules. Here is an  example site that uses CSS modules . What is a CSS module…","timeToRead":1,"fields":{"slug":"/docs/css-modules/","anchor":"css-modules"},"frontmatter":{"title":"CSS Modules","overview":null,"issue":null},"parent":{"__typename":"File","relativePath":"docs/css-modules.md"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/docs/css-modules/"}}